sub_unit.name: Ontario
sub_unit.note: The Greenleaf's New York Journal, and Patriotic Register (New York, NY) lists 351 votes for Daniel Miles.

The Albany Gazette (Albany, NY) reports three towns as "No Name". The Original Towns in Ontario County when it was organized on January 27, 1789 were: Bristol, Bloomfield, Canandaigua, Easton, Middletown, Phelps and Seneca. By the state elections in late April 1796 these new towns appear to have been organized: Erwin, Honeoye[April 5, 1796], Jerusalem, Northfield, Sparta, Williamson[Sodus]. It appears the no name towns listed in the 1796 election returns were Bristol, Easton and Phelps.
